# Address PR Comments

When the user asks you to address PR comments (CodeRabbit, Cubic, Bugbot, human review, or CI feedback on an open PR):

1. **Fix** valid findings on the PR branch.
2. **Test** — run targeted tests for the changed areas; fix failures before pushing.
3. **Update the PR** — `git add`, `git commit`, and `git push` to the PR branch when fixes are complete.

Do **not** ask whether to commit or push after addressing PR comments. That is the expected end state.

## Exceptions

- Do not commit unrelated work that was not part of addressing the PR comments.
- If a finding is invalid or needs a product decision, note it in the PR or reply to the user — do not block the whole batch on one ambiguous item unless the user says to stop.
- Still follow `no-direct-main-merge`: push to the feature branch only; never merge or enable auto-merge autonomously (see that rule).
